The artists I've excluded from this updated upload, are The Isaacs. If you wish, you can check why if you follow this link and download:
 &lt;a href=&quot;
http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/4919381&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot; target=&quot;_NEW&quot;&gt;
http://thepiratebay.se/torrent/4919381&lt;/a&gt;

I've not excluded anyone else, no matter what you and I or anyone else think or know about how Christian every artist represented are, because that's not the point with these compilations.
For instance there's a song here performed by Tom Waits, and some might argue that he leads a different life than a Christian is supposed to lead. But we don't know that. And he has, as far as I know, never said that he does live like a Christian.
Bob Dylan is also in here, and many regard him as &quot;backslidden&quot;, and they may be right, but at least he's no hypocrite.
I could give you more examples, but I guess you get my point.

The reason for removing the Isaacs from the compilations, is that they appear so angelic and talk and sing like they're really, really Christian, while they secretly follow other teachings than the Words of Jesus of Nazareth. I hate that. I'd love to be proved wrong, but the research I've done and what I found speaks so loud, that I don't think I will, I'm afraid..

Not long ago I was backslidden myself, but I was once again saved by the Shepherd Jesus Christ's love and forgiveness. Now I'm back. Not by any means perfect, but I believe and act according to the Faith and mercy I've been given. During that period, I didn't pretend that everything was all right, which you can see by looking at the uploads and comments I made then. I'm not proud about it, but that's the truth.

With that said, I hereby re-upload the revised series as a RAR-pack, for those with limited and often expensive bandwidth, with all three included. They're all mp3, sampled between 160-320 kbps, tagged properly, so they'll play as well on your mp3-player and computer as they will if you burn them onto regular CD-Rs.. :-)

